rComments: Nice nice nice guy Wants us to learn and succeed. Class was focused on assignments and so he devoted half of our class time to go around and answer our questions about the assignments. So we were working on rough drafts and he was there to help us with them. Seriously nicest prof at UofT.

Not a good professor. He is just biased that education is important- not open to any other opinion. he said we would get a 10 on 10 if we had almost complete essay for the rough draft submission. i had a completed paper but only got an 8 which was really unfair. He also graded us very hard on the midterm.
Awesome prof.  Really nice guy, very helpful and knowledgable.
Nice enough guy, but a terrible, terrible Prof!!!  May look good on paper, but some people just aren't good Profs.  Extremely unorganized.
I think he was intimidated by the students. He was pretty helpful if u go to his office hours. But he could have gone into a bit more depth of the topics becuz the exam wanted more detailed answers.
he's a nice guy, but makes a lot of mistakes, bailey is better (though not nice)
Very good prof - much better than Bailey
